cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE 

The paper discusses the use of attention-based RNN models in computer vision, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence and machine learning. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely category. The paper also discusses natural language processing, which falls under cs.CL (Computation and Language). The attention mechanism is a popular technique in deep learning, which is covered in cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses the use of RNNs, which is a subfield of neural networks, covered in cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper discusses the use of deep learning models for various applications, which is covered in cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
